# v1.58
PATCH_v158_NOTES = "PROP-SLUG FIX + LIVE PAUSED ON EVIDENCE. (1) BUG: GRID LoL slugs use -game-handicap (no digit) which the single-map regex missed -> the bot placed REAL orders on handicap markets with fictitious edges (series prob vs handicap price; one $15 fill). Regex now catches all prop forms (handicap/kill/total/first-x/-game-). (2) Tier index now rebuilds DAILY (was weekly) - tier unknown was skipping legit fades mid-week (42 skips). (3) THE BIG FINDING - LIVE CALIBRATION REFEREE (108 resolved shadow-compared signals): market Brier .216 < Elo .243 < v2 .255 - on the current GRID-era academy-tier population the MARKET beats both models and v2 is WORST (backtest inverse). Both models overconfident (v2 hi-conf: predicted 73pct, actual 64pct). Legit v1.57-era fades went 0-5 (-\$75); median live gate edge 0.244 vs backtest ~0.13 = miscalibration masquerading as edge. ACTION: paused.flag SET (new LIVE fades halted; positions managed; all data streams running). Resume = delete output/esports_fade/paused.flag. Path forward: re-fit gate on GRID-era markets only / require data-rich matchups / shrink model toward market. Previous v1.57: MODEL V2 + DECISION LAYER (Cowork v2 pass, independently verified & retrained natively). (1) predict.py now serves the 5-seed HistGradientBoosting ensemble (cs2: v1 features; lol: +roster-staleness features) — OOS: CS2 .6554 acc/.2150 Brier/.0115 ECE (vs v1 .652/.2157/.0159); numbers reproduced locally after full retrain (sklearn-skew eliminated). Also FIXED a fuzzy-matcher false positive (junk queries matched 4-char teams -> confident probs for nonexistent teams; now requires >=60% containment coverage). (2) v2 DECISION LAYER in the gate — the money finding: tier/map/roster as FEATURES hurt edge (they make the model agree with the market, P=0.04 paired bootstrap) but as a BET FILTER they print: entry>0.20 (<=20c bucket = -64% at quoted prices) + CS2 tier known & non-S (unknown -16%, tier-S -5.7%). OOS filtered mid-range 5-15c: v2 +6.1% vs v1 +1.4% vs Elo -1.4%; all >=5c +10.7%. Filter fit pre-Feb, evaluated once Feb-Jun. (3) LIVE TIER FEED: analysis/build_tier_index.py -> tier_index.parquet from the weekly bo3 dump (21,434 pairs incl upcoming); bot hot-loads, _tier_for() resolves by team-pair+date. LoL gets the price rule only (no LoL tier feed). Previous: v1.56 maker-first."

# v1.56
PATCH_v156_NOTES = "MAKER-FIRST EXECUTION (Ship #3 — the last unshipped war-room item). Measured mean fill cost was ~1.7c/fill (533 fills) ≈ most of the raw fade edge; at a 3-8% net edge, execution alone ~doubles it. Gated fades now post GTC AT the signal price (maker, no +1c) with a 90s rest-then-cancel, and pay the +1c taker slippage ONLY when model_edge >= 0.15 (the edge covers the spread) or when no edge reading exists. Never chases on maker timeout — chasing spread on a thin edge is how the pre-v1.54 config bled. exec_mode (maker/taker) + model_edge are tagged on live_order events AND live_orders.jsonl for the adverse-selection check (compare maker-fill WR vs taker WR after ~100 fills; kill switch MAKER_FIRST_ENABLED=0). ALSO this session: in-play +40% on 122 paper bets DECOMPOSED — all 5 go/no-go gates pass BUT win-rate-vs-price binomial is only p=0.05 (contrarian <=0.30) resting on ~3 excess wins -> NOT live; stays paper with pre-registered revisit at contrarian n>=100 & p<0.02. Alchemy monthly cap reset confirmed (restart reconnects). Previous: v1.55 net-widening."

# v1.55
PATCH_v155_NOTES = "NET-WIDENING: LoL GOES LIVE + all-esports data pipeline + book-depth guard. (1) LoL LIVE: both pre-registered go-live gates passed on 155 observe-only samples (median book depth \$318, 71% fillable at bet size; would_fade=28 -> edge exists at threshold). LoL fades now route through the SAME v1.54 model-edge gate (v2 LoL model primary, edge>=0.10, Elo fallback) + all existing caps. The observe stream still logs EVERY LoL signal (feeds backtest_lol.py). Kill switch: LOL_OBSERVE_ONLY=1 env reverts to observe-only. (2) BOOK-DEPTH GUARD on every gated fade (all games): skip if ask-side depth within 2c < bet (skip_thin_book event) — with entries allowed to 0.10 and a second live game, never fire into an empty book; Kelly reuses the same book call. (3) ALL-ESPORTS PIPELINE: pandascore_download/flatten/build_elo now accept dota2/valorant/rl/ow/codmw/r6siege; run_allgames_download.bat (task AllGamesDownload) pulls full history + builds validated Elo for each, so a model is ready the moment GRID lists H2H markets (the monitor alerts when they appear). Previous: v1.54 turnaround."

# v1.54
PATCH_v154_NOTES = "TURNAROUND — the live fade was losing -1.5% (VERIFIED on 567 real fills); this fixes it with two independently-validated changes. SHIP #1 MODEL-EDGE GATE: the model filter now GATES on the v2 gradient-boosted Predictor (was Elo), threshold raised 0.07->0.10, and the entry-price floor lowered 0.20->0.10. Validated three ways (feasibility_joined +20.6% @3c at edge>=0.10 monotonic; strictly-OOS REPORT.md backtest; live shadow A/B where model-pass +79% vs Elo-pass +63%). Falls back to Elo when v2 can't price a matchup; if v2 failed to load it uses Elo throughout (fail-safe). Low-price model-confirmed entries were the ONLY profitable segment (+17.8%), so the floor was blocking the edge — the gate does the quality control now. SHIP #2 TOXIC-WALLET FILTER (identify_active_targets): drop any wallet we've faded >=20x at a net loss on real fills — self-maintaining from live_results.csv. This alone flips the operation: the entire -$96 loss was ONE high-frequency wallet (0x47138dc1: 95 fills, -10.1%); without it the rest is ~breakeven, and the gate takes it positive. Next: quarter-Kelly sizing (after the gate proves out) + a price-capture logger to unblock prop/arb backtests. Previous: v1.53 shadow A/B (observational)."

# v1.53
PATCH_v153_NOTES = "SHADOW A/B of the Cowork esports_model win-prob model (NO trading change). Loads the gradient-boosted Predictor (esports_model/) and, on every CS2 fade that reaches the live Elo filter, logs a 'shadow_compare' event with BOTH models' prob/edge/pass-decision (and whether they agree) — so we can measure whether the new model beats the live Elo filter on real decisions before ever trusting it with money. PURELY OBSERVATIONAL: the trade decision stays 100% on the existing Elo filter; the shadow path is fully exception-wrapped and disabled-on-failure (SHADOW_MODEL_ENABLED, fail-safe if sklearn/artifacts missing), so trading is unaffected no matter what. Predictor reproduces Cowork's numbers locally (CS2 0.652 acc, +74% edge at 15c) and resolves 98% of real CS2 / 93% of LoL market matchups via an added alias table. Next: accumulate shadow_compare data, then evaluate which model is more accurate/profitable on resolved markets before any go-live. Previous: v1.52 reserve CS2 target slots."

# v1.52
PATCH_v152_NOTES = "RESERVE CS2 TARGET SLOTS — fix CS2 live targets crowded to ZERO by the GRID LoL explosion. GRID listed ~54k LoL markets; the v1.51 target classifier correctly captured their losing bettors as 'league', but ranked by worst ROI they consumed the ENTIRE 300-wallet LIVE cap -> CS2 dropped to 0 live targets, silently killing live trading (CS2 is the only LIVE-tradeable game; LoL is observe-only). Fix (identify_active_targets): take ALL qualifying CS2 wallets FIRST, then fill the remaining cap with league/other. CS2 qualifiers are few (~tens) so LoL still gets the bulk for observe-only detection. Restores CS2 live targeting while keeping LoL coverage. Previous: v1.51 LoL readiness hardening."

# v1.51
PATCH_v151_NOTES = "LoL READINESS HARDENING — be 100% ready to capture League the moment GRID lists markets, with zero manual steps. Five pre-emptive fixes against the ways we'd otherwise miss it: (1) PERIODIC TOKEN-INDEX RELOAD (maybe_reload_token_index, called from the loop) — the bot built token_index ONCE at startup and went blind to new markets (a 3-day process had missed ~1,400 tokens); now it hot-reloads the parquet on mtime change, so new CS2/LoL markets are detected without a restart. THE #1 miss-risk, fixed. (2) build_clob_index LoL patterns widened ('lol-','arch-lol-') so GRID head-to-head slugs get indexed (Valorant unaffected). (3) identify_active_targets game classifier maps ALL LoL slug variants (lol-/arch-lol-/league-of-legends/-lol-) to 'league' (Valorant excluded) so LoL bettors are captured regardless of GRID's slug format (was slug.split('-')[0], which mislabeled them). (4) Model routing _model_for_slug + lol_model.maybe_reload(): the live model filter now routes CS2->cs2_model, LoL->lol_model — CS2 behaviour identical — so a LoL go-live is a clean LOL_OBSERVE_ONLY flip (still OFF). (5) LoL Elo daily refresh task keeps lol_*.parquet current; bot hot-reloads it. Verified: model routing + index patterns + target classifier all correct; CS2 path unchanged. Previous: v1.50 LoL observe-only wiring."

# v1.50
PATCH_v150_NOTES = "LoL OBSERVE-ONLY paper wiring (no real money on League). Built a validated LoL Elo model (65.5% acc, Brier 0.215, 20,878 matches) via the CS2 pipeline parameterized by game. This patch makes the LIVE bot OBSERVE LoL opportunities without trading them, to settle the open questions (live model edge + order-book liquidity — the mirage that killed CS2 pre-match) at zero risk. Changes: (1) load self.lol_model = CS2Model(game='lol') alongside cs2_model; (2) _is_lol_slug() detects LoL and EXCLUDES Valorant VCT (whose slugs contain 'league' — audit-found contamination); (3) process_trade routes LoL slugs to _observe_lol() which prices via the LoL model, logs LIVE book depth via _clob_book(), writes output/esports_fade/lol_observations.csv + a lol_observation event, and RETURNS without placing — CS2/CSGO live path unchanged; (4) on-chain gate (_load_cs2_windows) extended to open during LoL match windows too (Valorant excluded) so the listener detects LoL; (5) ESPORTS_PREFIXES + heartbeat lol_obs counter. LIVE LoL stays OFF (LOL_OBSERVE_ONLY=True). Audit confirmed the game-agnostic fixes (entry floor, phantom exposure, fade-SELL pricing, name-collision) already protect LoL; top LoL teams match 100%, 235/294 historical H2H markets matchable. Previous: v1.49 fade-of-SELL mispricing fix."

# v1.49
PATCH_v149_NOTES = "FADE-OF-SELL MISPRICING FIX (4th blocker; orders placed but never filled). When fading a target's SELL we correctly buy the SAME outcome they sold, but our_entry was computed as (1 - their_price) for BOTH the BUY and SELL branches. For the SELL branch that's the COMPLEMENT price: e.g. target sold Vitality @0.705, we'd bid 1-0.705=0.295 for the Vitality token (which trades ~0.705) -> the bid sat far below market and was canceled unfilled (3 vit-fal2 orders, 0 shares, 2026-06-18). It ALSO corrupted the Elo model edge: model_p(Vitality)=0.66 vs bogus 0.295 entry = fake +0.37 edge that PASSED the filter; with the correct 0.705 entry the edge is ~-0.04 and is correctly rejected. Fix: fade-SELL branch uses our_entry = their_price (the bought outcome's own price). Net effect: fade-of-SELL orders now price at market (can fill) AND the model filter sees the true edge (only real-edge fades trade). Fade-of-BUY unchanged (1-their_price is correct there). Previous: v1.48 phantom-exposure fix."

# v1.48
PATCH_v148_NOTES = "PHANTOM-EXPOSURE FIX (3rd zero-trades blocker). market_exposure (read by the per-market $ cap AND the opposite-side hedge guard) was incremented at SIGNAL time (process_trade, before placement). So any signal that was then floored, errored, or never filled left fake $ on that (market,outcome) — which then blocked the whole market: furia-9z showed $45 exposure + opposite-side block with ZERO real orders in live_orders.jsonl/live_results.csv (verified). Fix: in LIVE mode market_exposure is incremented ONLY on a confirmed matched fill inside place_live_order (by actual matched cost); the signal-time increment now runs for PAPER only. Makes the cap + hedge guard reflect REAL positions. A restart also clears the stranded phantom (rebuilt from live_orders = $0). NOTE: per-wallet daily-fade counter still counts attempts (separate, smaller issue; not changed). Combined with v1.47 (model name-collision + floor 0.40->0.20), this clears all three identified blockers behind 2 days of no trades. Previous: v1.47 model name-collision + entry floor."

# v1.47
PATCH_v147_NOTES = "TWO fixes after 48h of ZERO live orders despite 1066 target signals. (1) CS2 MODEL NAME-COLLISION BUG: name_to_id was first-writer-wins, so when two teams normalize to the same key (e.g. 'Team Falcons' [308 games] and a minor 'Falcons' [7 games] both -> 'falcons') the low-games minor team often claimed it -> predict() returned low_games -> EVERY real matchup against that team was wrongly skipped as skip_model_unmatched. Over 48h this blocked 238 series-moneyline fades across 5 matchups (vit-fal2 x89, tdk-nem x116, sparta-inox x10, ...). Fix: CS2Model._register() resolves name collisions by PREFERRING THE HIGHER-GAMES TEAM (the established roster), which is the intended team for a market. Verified: Vitality/Falcons, TDK/Nemiga, Sparta/Inox now evaluate ok=True. Affects all 3 model-using bots. (2) ENTRY-PRICE FLOOR LIVE_MIN_OUR_ENTRY 0.40->0.20: the 0.40 floor (from a 0/5 pre-model-filter sample) was killing ALL 10 model-APPROVED fades in 48h (underdog buys 0.25-0.39). The v1.41 model filter now does the value-screening the floor crudely proxied, so 0.40 redundantly blocked the strategy's best setups; 0.20 keeps only an extreme-longshot guard. Daily loss/risk caps still bound downside. Previous: v1.46 on-chain gate to live CS2 windows."

# v1.46
PATCH_v146_NOTES = "On-chain listener now POLLS ONLY DURING LIVE CS2 MATCH WINDOWS (Alchemy CU fix #2, no trading-logic change). After v1.45 slowed polling to 15s, the bigger waste remained: we poll eth_getLogs 24/7 even though most of the day has no live CS2 match. New gate (esports_fade_bot._onchain_gate, passed to OnChainListener) builds match windows from clob_esports_markets.parquet — a REAL CS2 match market has a populated game_start (prop/futures like 'will-cs2-market-cap-...' don't, which cleanly excludes them); window = [game_start - 2h, game_start + 5h]. When no window is open the listener makes ZERO RPC calls and just re-checks every 5 min. Measured duty cycle across the live dataset = ~31% active, so on-chain CU burn drops ~3x (from ~1M to ~310K CU/day; 30M lasts ~3 months). SAFETY: the gate fails OPEN on any error or before first load (never silently blinds detection), buffers are generous so pre-match/long Bo5s aren't missed, and the data-api poll still backstops any window we misjudge. Worst case of a gate bug = a missed fade, never a financial loss. Heartbeat now shows gate=active|IDLE(no-cs2). Disable via ONCHAIN_GATE_ENABLED=0. Previous: v1.45 POLL_INTERVAL 3s->15s."

# v1.45
PATCH_v145_NOTES = "On-chain listener POLL_INTERVAL 3s->15s (CU-budget fix, no trading-logic change). The Alchemy key hit its 30M CU spending cap in ~6 days: 3s eth_getLogs polling 24/7 (2 getLogs + 1 blockNumber per poll, ~160 CU) = ~5M CU/day. Alchemy now returns 429; the listener auto-rotated to the free public-RPC fallbacks (conn stays True, detections still climbing) but they're flaky (frequent Read timeouts, lag ~14s vs ~3s on Alchemy). Rather than pay to raise the cap for a fade edge that's currently ~0 (daily PnL $0, strategy under reconsideration), slowed polling to 15s -> ~1M CU/day so 30M lasts a full month, and cut the public-RPC thrash now. Detection latency ~15s is still ~15x better than the ~220s data-api the on-chain path replaced, so it's a non-issue at a flat edge. Bigger future win (NOT done here, one-change-at-a-time): gate polling to active CS2 match windows only. Revert toward 3-5s if the edge proves real and the CU budget is raised. Previous: v1.44 infra/robustness audit."

# v1.44
PATCH_v144_NOTES = "Infra/robustness audit (no trading-logic change). Found+fixed a class of SILENT-FAILURE bugs from unverified external-data assumptions: (1) in-play bot detected live matches via bo3 `state` field, but the live flag is `status`=current -> saw 0 live matches forever (also fixed norm() dropping short-name teams like '9z Team', and parse_teams leaving '(BO3)-<event>' suffixes). In-play now works end-to-end: first paper bets, bo3 latency 89s, depth ~$80. (2) WATCHDOG STALE-LOCK TRAP: every watch_*.bat exited on an existing lock file; when a bot+watchdog died together (crash/reboot) the leftover lock blocked all restarts -> cs2_model paper bot silently dead 2 days, and on REBOOT would block EVERY onstart watchdog incl. the LIVE esports bot. Fixed all watchdogs to self-heal (delete stale lock; schtasks IgnoreNew default prevents double-run). Verified CLOB order-status checks already use .lower() (no MATCHED-case bug); no bo3 script filters on the unreliable `state` field. Previous: v1.43 lowered MODEL_FILTER_MIN_EDGE 0.10->0.07."

# v1.43
PATCH_v143_NOTES = "Lowered MODEL_FILTER_MIN_EDGE 0.10 -> 0.07. The v1.41 model filter was so selective that the live bot placed only ~7 orders on ~3-4 unique markets over 48h (heavy reductions from single-map skips, market-$ caps, hedge guard, and the 8% model-gate pass rate). That's correct/by-design but validates the fade+model edge too slowly (weeks for a sample). Backtest (fade+model) was positive below the 0.10 threshold too (thr 0.0 +13.8%, 0.10 +30%, 0.15 +42.5%), so dropping to 0.07 trades a bit of per-bet edge for ~2-3x the volume = a real sample this month. Everything else unchanged; revisit the threshold once we have OOS live data. Previous: v1.42 stall detector counts target signals (pre-filter) not placed fades."

# v1.42
PATCH_v142_NOTES = "Stall detector counts TARGET SIGNALS SEEN (pre-filter), not placed fades. After v1.41's model filter, placed fades are rare by design, so the old fades-based stall detector cried wolf — firing 'signal stall' Telegram alerts whenever the filter was simply being selective. New self.target_signals_seen counter increments for every genuine target-wallet signal that reaches the fade logic (after wallet+market validation, BEFORE the model filter / caps / single-map filter). The stall detector now alarms only when target activity genuinely stops (dead feed / no matches) for SIGNAL_STALL_SECONDS, regardless of how many fades the model filter places. Heartbeat now shows both signals= (pre-filter) and fades= (placed). No change to order placement. Previous: v1.41 Elo MODEL FILTER on the live fade bot (fade+model hybrid)."

# v1.41
PATCH_v141_NOTES = "Elo MODEL FILTER on the live fade bot (fade+model hybrid). A PandaScore-fed CS2 Elo model was backtested against Polymarket prices: betting when the model disagrees with the market by >0.10 returned +13-19% ROI out-of-sample after friction. Combining it with the fade signal beat either alone: on CS2 series markets with target activity, fading ONLY when the model also likes our side returned +30% ROI (vs +19% model-only, +10% fade-only) — because the fade signal tells us WHEN the model's edge is real (a known loser is on the other side). v1.41 adds MODEL_FILTER_ENABLED: a LIVE fade is now placed only if cs2_model.predict() says our fade side is under-priced by > MODEL_FILTER_MIN_EDGE (0.10). CS2/CSGO markets where teams can't be matched, and non-CS2 markets (LoL — no model), are SKIPPED on LIVE with a logged event. PAPER mode is unaffected (still logs all fades for data collection). Model Elo is hot-reloaded hourly (analysis/refresh_elo.py). This converges the on-chain fast fade (v1.40, ~2s detection) with the Elo value check into the strongest backtested config. Standalone CS2 model paper bot (cs2_model_bot.py) also running in parallel to validate the model independently + capture live order-book liquidity."

# v1.40
PATCH_v140_NOTES = "On-chain real-time signal source (latency fix). Diagnostic proved 99.7% of signal latency is the Polymarket data-api /trades feed being ~220s stale (median 108s their-fill->we-see-it, p90 280s); our processing+signing+network is 0.5s total, so a VPS would do nothing. 27% of target signals were missed entirely as stale, and 77% of acted trades were >60s old by the time we faded — almost certainly why the edge decayed to ~0 (we arrive after the market absorbs the target's bad bet). FIX: new onchain_listener.py watches Polygon for ERC-1155 TransferSingle events on the Conditional Tokens contract (0x4d97...6045) filtered to our target wallets via eth_getLogs every 2s. Proxy wallet appears as indexed to (BUY) / from (SELL) topic; token id + shares in data. Decode validated 100% on side+outcome vs data-api ground truth. Price via CLOB midpoint at detection (skip if unavailable/out of range). Detection latency ~2-4s vs ~108-280s = 30-50x faster. Runs as a background thread feeding a queue the main loop drains into the SAME process_trade pipeline (all gates apply: entry floor, per-wallet cap, single-map filter, hedge guard, daily loss cap). data-api poll stays as backstop; dedup by tx hash means whichever source sees a trade first wins. Orders are LIMIT at our computed entry so a price error cannot overpay. RPC configurable via POLYGON_RPC_URL env (defaults to public endpoints). This is the test of whether low latency revives the edge — monitor closely; if edge stays dead at 2s the CS2 fade is not exploitable and we stop."

# v1.39
PATCH_v139_NOTES = "Three esports fade fixes after a -$240/3-day bleed. Deep diagnostic on 415 live trades found the trade-weighted edge is -1.3% (win rate tracks entry price almost exactly = efficiently-priced market, no durable alpha). The first 11 days' +$36 was variance; we scaled $10->$15 at the luck peak (v1.35) then mean-reverted. Root cause of concentrated losses: (1) wallet 0x47138dc1 was faded 90x (22% of all volume) for -$109 — it's a MARKET MAKER (95,730 trades, -11% naive ROI; MMs capture spread and look mildly negative on directional PnL). (2) single-map/Bo1 markets are coin flips (-8.1% ROI vs -3.5% series). FIXES: (a) MAX_FADES_PER_WALLET_PER_DAY=3 so no wallet dominates; (b) SKIP_SINGLE_MAP_MARKETS via is_single_map_market() regex; (c) rebuilt target list — exclude bot/MM wallets trading >30/day (removed 91, incl 3 with POSITIVE ROI we'd been fading), rank LIVE subset by ROI ascending not absolute pnl (old ranking surfaced high-volume bots), tighten to ROI<-15% AND recent_roi<-5%, cap 300 (was 800), require recent-window persistence. New list hot-reloaded live (300 wallets, -500 dropped, toxic MM gone). Did NOT add price-band filter (overfit, no mechanism). Bet size stays $15 per user. Honest read: edge is marginal; these fixes remove the worst structural leaks but the strategy is close to break-even on directional accounting."

# v1.38
PATCH_v138_NOTES = "MLB live trading DISABLED. After v1.36 deployed MLB at $5/trade on 2026-05-27, the first ~24h bled hard despite paper data showing +7-10% ROI over 355 trades. User halted via /pause and asked to disable. Set LIVE_SPORTS_PREFIXES = () so no sport is live-eligible — every signal falls back to paper logging. Sports bot continues running for ongoing data collection on NHL/Tennis/NBA/MLB; nothing places real money. Esports bot unaffected. Pre-deploy paper +7% ROI did not survive live execution friction; needs investigation before any sport is re-enabled."

# v1.37
PATCH_v137_NOTES = "Fix opposite-side hedge bug recurrence. The v1.34-era opposite-side hedge guard (don't buy both sides of a binary market) relied on self.market_exposure[(cid, outcome)] being populated. But (a) market_exposure was reset to empty at every UTC day rollover via market_exposure.clear() and (b) was never persisted across bot restarts. Discovered on cs2-3dmax-mgc-2026-05-27 where we bought 3DMAX at 17:24 UTC, then UTC midnight wiped the exposure dict, then bought magic at 01:44 UTC the next day for a guaranteed loss of -$1.15. Two changes: (1) removed market_exposure.clear() from day rollover (positions persist across days), (2) added _rebuild_market_exposure() called at startup that scans live_orders.jsonl, subtracts matched SELLs, and excludes already-resolved markets (per live_results.csv). Applied to both esports_fade_bot.py and sports_fade_bot.py. Net dollar damage from this specific instance: -$1.15 worst case on the locked dual-side position; bug had been latent since v1.34 hedge guard was added 2026-05-24."

# v1.36
PATCH_v136_NOTES = "Sports fade bot enters LIVE mode (MLB only). After 4 days of paper data on the v2 sports bot (1095 resolved trades), MLB held the cleanest signal: +7.2% ROI over 355 trades with 58.6% win rate. Tennis collapsed from +2.5% to -19.3% on May 27 (single-day blowup, 311 new trades net -$581) and is excluded from LIVE. NBA still +10.6% but season ending; NHL sample too small (34 trades). MLB-only deployment at $5/trade. Strategy: bot now accepts --live flag (was forcibly PAPER before). When --live is on AND market slug starts with LIVE_SPORTS_PREFIXES ('mlb-'), bot places real CLOB orders via the same place_live_order pipeline as esports_fade_bot. When --live is on but slug isn't MLB, bot falls back to paper logging - data collection on NHL/Tennis/NBA continues uninterrupted. DAILY_LOSS_CAP for sports lowered 150->75 (sport LIVE bankroll is independent from esports). New evaluate_sports_live.py mirrors esports evaluate_live.py but writes to output/sports_fade/ paths. New scheduled task PolyBotSportsLiveEval runs every 10 min to refresh live_daily_pnl.json so the sports bot's loss cap can fire. Watch_sports_fade.bat now launches with --live. Wallet shared with esports for now - data ledgers are fully separate (output/sports_fade vs output/esports_fade). Starting bet size $5/trade; bump after ~200 live trades hold positive ROI."
